headline: You Can Do Better Than a 3.8% Yield: These 2 Dividend Stocks Are Buys Today
summary: The S&P 500 index (SNPINDEX: ^GSPC), for example, has an itty bitty 1.3% dividend yield even after a swift sell-off.  At first glance, you could do better with Citigroup (NYSE: C), a highly regarded bank that has a much higher 3.8% yield.  Citigroup has an above-market and above-bank-average dividend yield.
